category: Consumer Products Named After Astronomical Terms
explanation: Galaxy (chocolate bar), Eclipse (chewing gum), Comet (cleanser), and Orion (snack brand) are all consumer products or brands named after astronomical objects or phenomena. Jupiter is an actual planet, not a product named after one.

Hamlet, Othello, King Lear, and Macbeth are the titular protagonists of four of William Shakespeare's most renowned tragedies. Falstaff is a prominent comedic character appearing in several of Shakespeare's historical plays and one comedy, not a major tragedy.
All tokens except 'Thumb' are human body parts that also have a common homophone (Eye/I, Ear/Hear, Nose/Knows, Toe/Tow). 'Thumb' is a body part but does not have a commonly recognized homophone.
